comb
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:in shearing, the lower, stationary unit of shearing handpiece which enters and holds the wool as it is cut
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:wide comb, narrow comb
Pronunciation:
